    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.7.0-dev+1416-g012c05580\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nVoid lInux (glibc)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty 0.10.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppImage\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:Man /us/lib/erlang/man/man4/app.4\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe man page should open in a separate window, rendered properly.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nAn error is raised:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError detected while processing function man#open_page:\r\nline   38:\r\nE426: tag not found: app(4)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe same behaviour happens with other non-standard man pages, not just those from Erlang. I have a little WIP project ([ips-tools](https://gitlab.com/HiPhish/IPS-Tools)) and I would like to render its man pages in Neovim using `:Man ./man/man1/ips.1`. The same error message appears.\r\n\r\nOpening standard man pages on the other hand works without issue using the equivalent command `:Man /usr/share/man/man1/bash.1`.",
