            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "`:Man {path}`\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/0806c882cdeb1d07006c7dec843cec68dc3fe7f4/runtime/doc/filetype.txt#L605-L606\r\ndoes not work (NVIM 57ce6c2b8ff1dc3045f6e6be325d3e6b6b4fb15c; oh `--version` no longer prints hash).\r\n\r\n# How to reproduce\r\n\r\nGo to `/tmp` and prepare `ls.1` with the following content:\r\n```man\r\n.TH ThisIsTitle \"1\"\r\n.SH DESCRIPTION\r\nDo you read me?\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen:\r\n\r\n| command | works as expected? |\r\n|--|--|\r\n| `MANPAGER='nvim --clean +Man!' man ./ls.1`  | Y: opens the above file |\r\n| `MANPAGER='nvim --clean +Man!' man $PWD/ls.1` | Y: opens the above file |\r\n| `nvim --clean -c \"Man ./ls.1\"` | N: opens system man, `/usr/share/man/man1/ls.1.gz` |\r\n| `nvim --clean -c \"Man $PWD/ls.1\"` | N: opens system man, `/usr/share/man/man1/ls.1.gz` |\r\n\r\nIf the file is copied to `x.1`, which must not exist in `MANPATH`, then\r\n\r\n| command | works as expected? |\r\n|--|--|\r\n| `nvim --clean -c \"Man ./x.1\"` | N: opens `xasy(1)` |\r\n| `nvim --clean -c \"Man $PWD/x.1\"` | N: opens `xasy(1)` |",
